			<div class="grop-of-options">
				<h3 id="configuration-page-title">1. Configuration page</h3>
				<div id="global-options-section" class="awards">
					<p>In this page, the global options of the experiment can be chosen. These options are indicated in the configuration file as a headline. Here, those options are explained one by one.</p>
					<section>
						<h2 id="main-options-title">1.1 Main Options</h2>
						<p>Here are included the most basic configuration options of the experiment. Those options are explaind below.</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>File name:</strong> Is the name that the file will have</li>
							<li><strong>Output to ascii:</strong> Indicates if is wanted to output the data of the experiment to an Ascii text file.</li>
							<li><strong>Continuous running:</strong> Without this option, DMDX will pause after each item and wait for the subject to request the next item.</li>
							<li id="standrad-duration-explanation"><strong>Standard frame duration:</strong> This option indicates how long to display each stimulus for. Is measured in <a href="#ticks-explanation">ticks</a>.</li>
							<li><strong>Delay:</strong> Indicates the delay from end of one item to the start of the next item. Is measured in <a href="#ticks-explanation">ticks</a>.</li>
							<li><strong>Time out:</strong> This option tells DMDX how lon to wait for subjects to make a response. Measured in <u>milliseconds</u>.</li>
							<li><strong>Video mode:</strong> The parameters of this field indicates the following: <ol>
								<li>Number of pixels horizontally</li>
								<li>Number of pixels vertically</li>
								<li>Number of scan lines</li>
								<li>Number of bits of colour</li>
								<li>Refresh rate</li>
							</ol></li>
							<li><strong>No feed back:</strong> Indicates not to provide feedback on subjects response times and errors. Without this option, DMDX will display messages during the experiment, what can be too distracting for most of the tasks, but may be useful in some circumstances.</li>
							<li><strong>Default background color:</strong> Indicates the background color. <a href="#color-indication-explanation">See how to indicate colors</a></li>
							<li><strong>Default writing color:</strong> Indicates the color of the writing. <a href="#color-indication-explanation">See how to indicate colors</a></li>
							<li><strong>Default font size:</strong> Indicates the font size</li>
							<li><strong>Record clock on time keyword:</strong> If you include this in your header, DMDX will include the time of each clockon in your experiment. The first clockon will be set as 0 and all later will be relative to that.</li>
						</ul>
					</section>
					<section>
						<h2 id="response-devices-title">1.2. Response devices</h2>
						<p>In this part the method used to record responses is used. The method must be one of the ones below.</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>PIO12:</strong> The response box</li>
							<li><strong>Keyboard:</strong> The keyboard</li>
							<li><strong>Mouse:</strong> The mouse</li>
							<li><strong>DigitalVOX:</strong> A digital voice activated switch</li>
							<li><strong>Record vocal:</strong> Saves verbal responses as .wav files</li>
						</ul>
					</section>
				</div>
